AbstractWe prove the following quantitative form of a classical theorem of Steintiz: Letm be sufficiently large. If the convex hull of a subsetS of Euclideand-space contains a unit ball centered on the origin, then there is a subset ofS with at mostm points whose convex hull contains a solid ball also centered on the origin and havingresidual radius
